## Framework

- Use Vitest for unit and component tests
- Use Playwright for E2E tests
- Use React Testing Library for component tests

## File Organization

- Test files colocated next to source: `Component.tsx` → `Component.test.tsx`
- E2E tests in `e2e/` directory at project root
- Test utilities in `tests/utils/`

## Naming

- Describe behavior, not implementation: `"should display error when form is invalid"`
- Group related tests with `describe` blocks
- Use `it` or `test` consistently (prefer `it`)

## Patterns

- Arrange → Act → Assert structure
- One assertion per test when possible
- Mock external dependencies (API calls, database)
- Don't mock internal implementation details
- Test user-visible behavior, not internal state

## What to Test

- User interactions (clicks, form submissions)
- Conditional rendering (loading, error, empty states)
- Edge cases (empty data, very long strings, special characters)
- API error handling (network failures, 4xx/5xx responses)

## What NOT to Test

- Implementation details (internal state, private methods)
- Third-party library behavior
- Exact CSS styling
